  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nfeature maybe\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nCurrently all packages in react repo are bundled separately, but I notice that the common **shared** methods/file(e.x. the internal symbols, `invariant`, `warning`) are bundled to **every** package which use it, I mean these files belong to this repo rather than 3rd like `object-assign`, `prop-types` etc. \r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nSo, could we create a vendor(just like we do in an app) for the shared files between packages to reduce the size?\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n16.8.5 MacOS",
